    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - AIR-TO-AIR CHARGE AIR COOLER - TROUBLESHOOTING -
        SPRING-LOADED T-BOLT HOSE CLAMPS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl1200603" svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>SPRING-LOADED T-BOLT HOSE CLAMPS</title>
        <para>Because of extreme temperature changes, hoses will HEAT-SET, making the hose less resilient and the
            outside diameter smaller. This can cause the hose clamps to loosen and leak, resulting in vehicle power
            loss. Using spring-loaded T-bolt hose clamps will help prevent hose clamp failures.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
